         <abstract>
            <p>The study of the magnetohydrodynamic (MHD) stability of a plasma in a toroidal configuration leads to a problem of computing the spectrum of a noncompact selfadjoint operator $T$. The spectrum of $T$ will be approximated by the eigenvalues of $T_h$, a Galerkin approximation of $T$. We present a two-dimensional model problem with two components containing most difficulties arising in the physical problem. We give subspaces and prove sufficient conditions for obtaining convergence using partial regularity of $T$.</p>
          </abstract>
